Using state firms as battle spears gives the lie to China&rsquo;s claim that it is managing them according to market principles. And weaponising regulators undermines China&rsquo;s ambitions to play a bigger international role. The airline supervisor had earned respect in leading the charge to ground the 737 MAX, Boeing&rsquo;s troubled aeroplane; its Cathay warning makes it look like a political hack. The party may well get foreign companies to toe its line on Hong Kong. In the process it is revealing its true nature.■<br />
<br />
This article appeared in the Leaders section of the print edition under the headline&quot;Cathay&rsquo;s mayday&quot;
